Name: Yankee Supreme (CC26-1A)
Breeder: Reeves et al., University Maine, Campbell Institute.
Characteristics: not in production; medium yield of oblong, white tubers; medium-late maturity, good for tablestock, medium tuber solids, medium dormancy.
Resistance: PVX, net necrosis caused by pea leaf roll virus. American Potato Journal 61:683. 1983.

Name: York
Breeder: Canada Department of Agric., Guelph, Ontario.
Characteristics: early maturing, white skinned, high total solids.
Adaptation: organic soils of Ontario, Canada American Potato Journal 47(6), 1970.
Resistance: field immunity to virus X and common races of late blight; tolerance to common scab and rhizoctonia.

Name: Yukon Gold (G6666-4Y)
Breeder: Johnston and Rowberry, Ag. Canada, Ontario.
Characteristics: medium-high yield of oval, white tubers, with yellow flesh; early-medium maturity, good for tablestock, medium specific gravity, short dormancy, this cultivar is currently (1996) the predominant yellow-fleshed specialty potato, produced in small amounts throughout North America.
Resistance: PVA. American Potato Journal 58:241. 1980.
